President Barack Obama will hold a news conference on Wednesday, April 29th at 8:00PM EDT at the White House. Members of the media who wish to attend must apply for credentials by the deadline of today at 12:00PM EDT. This includes current White House hard pass holders. The application process requires providing personal information such as full name, date of birth, social security number, and country of citizenship. Riser positions have already been allocated, but a pool feed will be available. Applicants will be notified by 6:00PM EDT on Tuesday, April 28th if their credentials have been granted and will receive logistical information.